                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d769">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.00/662: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-13T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >July 13, 1931—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:52 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>67. Embassy’s telegram 64, July 11, noon. Garcesgana unsuccessful in forming
                    cabinet. Nonpolitical Coalition Ministry reduced to seven members announced this
                    evening with Pedro Blanquier as Premier and Minister of Finance. As Director
                    General of State Railways he showed great administrative ability and the
                    strength of the present cabinet lies exclusively in him.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
